<HL>
   Unisys Corp. Obtains
   $180.6 Million Job
   For Navy Upgrades
</HL>
<DATE>
09/28/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A7
</SO>
<CO>
   UIS GD ROK HON GQ MOT TXT BA GM GMH ITT CSC GTE
</CO>
<IN>
AEROSPACE (ARO)
</IN>
<GV>
DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)
</GV>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- Unisys Corp. said it received a $180.6
million Navy contract for targeting system improvements.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   OMI Bulk Transport Inc. got a $144.7 million Navy contract
for transport charters.
                                                                                                       

   General Dynamics Corp. was given contracts of $110.3
million for Army M-1 tanks and Navy aircraft.
                                                                                                       

   Honeywell Inc. was issued a $104.7 million job for Army
munitions.
                                                                                                       

   Rockwell International Corp. got an $83.3 million Air
Force contract for B-1B aircraft repair.
                                                                                                       

   Southern Air Transport Inc. was awarded a $54.1 million
Air Force contract for air transport services.
                                                                                                       

   Grumman Corp. won a $48.2 million Air Force contract for
F-111 aircraft components and Navy aircraft training
equipment.
                                                                                                       

   Motorola Inc. received a $36.9 million Navy contract for
Standard missile components.
                                                                                                       

   Avco Corp., a unit of Textron Inc., got a $35.4 million
Air Force contract for MX missile components.
                                                                                                       

   A joint venture of Textron Inc. and Boeing Co. received a
$31.5 million Navy contract for development of the V-22
aircraft.
   Boeing also received a $21.3 million Air Force contract
for engineering services. And the company's Boeing Computer
Services received a $15.8 million Army contract for
automation systems.
                                                                                                       

   Hughes Aircraft Co., a unit of General Motors Corp., was
awarded a $23.3 million Navy contract for a targeting system.
General Motors also got a $17.5 million Navy contract for
aircraft engines.
                                                                                                       

   Zantop International Airlines received a $23.2 million Air
Force contract for air transportation services.
                                                                                                       

   Martin-Baker Aircraft Co. was given a $19 million Navy
contract for aircraft ejection seats.
                                                                                                       

   ITT Corp. received an $18 million Army contract for a
radar jammer.
                                                                                                       

   Computer Sciences Corp. won a $15.3 million Army contract
for automation systems.
                                                                                                       

   Republic Corp. was issued a $14.7 million Air Force
contract for C-130 aircraft overhaul.
                                                                                                       

   GTE Government Systems Corp., a unit of GTE Corp., won a
$12 million Army contract for communications equipment.
</TEXT>
